442. Find All Duplicates in an Array
Given an integer array nums of length n where all the integers of nums are in the range [1, n] 
and each integer appears at most twice, return an array of all the integers that appears twice.
You must write an algorithm that runs in O(n) time and uses only constant auxiliary space, excluding the space needed to store the output

 
Example 1:
Input: nums = [4,3,2,7,8,2,3,1]
Output: [2,3]

Example 2:
Input: nums = [1,1,2]
Output: [1]

Example 3:
Input: nums = [1]
Output: []
 
Constraints:
n == nums.length
1 <= n <= 105
1 <= nums[i] <= n
Each element in nums appears once or twice.

Approach: Applying Cyclic Sort will move the duplicates element to the end of the array after some of the elements is sorted.
          So we can check for the elements that are not in the correct Index.

Solution: 
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> findDuplicates(int[] nums) {
        int i=0;
        while(i<nums.length){
            int crtIndex=nums[i]-1;
            if(nums[i]!= nums[crtIndex]){
                int temp=nums[i];
                nums[i]=nums[crtIndex];
                nums[crtIndex]=temp;
            }else{
                i++;
            }
        }
        //Finding all the duplicates - Duplicates will be positioned on wrong index.
        List<Integer> ans=new ArrayList<Integer>();
        for(int k=0;k<nums.length;k++){
            if(nums[k]!= k+1){
                ans.add(nums[k]);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
